      comments: 0,
      viralityScore: 50,
      script: "Consumer confidence right now is at levels we haven't seen since the Great Recession. And that's wild because we don't have mass layoffs. We don't have foreclosures piling up. The job market is soft but people still have jobs. So why does this matter to you as a Cape Coral buyer? Because low confidence makes people hesitate, and hesitation in this market creates opportunity. Here's the thing though: mortgage rates have historically been a stronger trigger than confidence. When rates dropped to three and four year lows in past cycles, buyers came back even when the headlines were scary. Cape Coral inventory is sitting right now, sellers are negotiating, and if rates tick down even slightly this summer, that window closes fast. The buyers who moved during low confidence periods are the ones who got the best deals. Are you planning to buy in Cape Coral this year or waiting? Tell me below and I'll show you what's available at your price point right now.",
      caption: "How does consumer confidence impact real estate? 🤔🏡 Lawrence Yun, NAR chief economist, breaks down what it means for buyers, sellers and the housing market right now.  Have a question for our economists? Email AskTheEconomist@nar.realtor or drop it in the comments below.",
