      script: "The sellers showed up to their own home inspection and decided it was the perfect time to take a shower. I am not kidding. This actually happened to us in Fort Myers last week. And here is the thing, in this market, you will see everything. Inspections in Fort Myers right now are turning up real surprises, roof damage from Ian that never got properly permitted, AC systems running 10 years past their lifespan, pool equipment that hasn't been touched since 2020. The buyers who come out ahead are the ones with an agent who doesn't panic, pivots fast, and knows exactly what to flag before you're locked in. I've closed 40 plus deals in Lee County and I have seen it all. So here's my question for you. Are you buying in Fort Myers this year, and do you actually know what to look for at your inspection? Drop your timeline below and I'll send you my personal inspection checklist, free.",
      caption: "Welp, on today’s episode of “Is this really my life?”  The sellers crashed our home inspection & decided it was the perfect time for a shower. 🧼 😭  Real Estate is SO FUN & there is NEVER a dull moment but learning to adapt in ANY environment and pivot under pressure is truly what sets me apart.  Today, I smiled. We pivoted & Thankfully we had a great inspection.   Bigggg THANK YOU to the 🐐 @essinpectsvalue for your PATIENCE & your attention to detail.   I can’t wait to see what the next inspection brings us 😂  #realtor #tampabay #realestate #inspector #realtorlife",
